                <td>QEC</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row">
                  Operation error
                  <span class="rp-cell-sub">imperfect gates and memory decoherence drop Bell-pair fidelity — purification trades pairs for higher fidelity; QEC corrects encoded errors</span>
                </th>
                <td>HEP</td>
                <td>QEC</td>
                <td>QEC</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <figcaption>
            HEG = heralded entanglement generation, HEP = heralded entanglement
            purification, QEC = quantum error correction. The shift from heralded
            (probabilistic, two-way classical signalling, retry-until-success) to
