        <h2>Network role</h2>
        <p>
          Repeaters are the network element that turns a two-node Bell-pair link into a
          long-haul service. Where the entanglement-distribution layer below them
          delivers Bell pairs across a single link, repeaters chain those links together
          to span continents. The choice of generation is a hardware-economics question:
          1G is what we can build today, 2G is what becomes available once logical
          memory qubits are below threshold, and 3G is what becomes available once
          high-loss-tolerant block codes can be processed at line rate at every
          station <SourceNote id="kumar-ijndc-2025" />.
        </p>
